Out[1]:

Table of 20 longest lived binaries in simulation of circular disks with different mass functions. The simulations have ~100 light stars of mass $5\times 10^{-5}$ and varying numbers of heavy stars. One simulation has a "super-heavy" stars that is 100 times more massive the light stars. Two other simulations have 3 or 10 stars that are 10 times heavier than the light stars. We also have a control simulation with no heavy stars.

For each set of parameters we perform an ensemble of 150 simulations. We have tried to run all simulations for 500 orbits to avoid biasing the binary statisitics (especially considering the stalled simulations may be precisely the ones that contain binaries). Nevertheless we still have one simulation missing from the set of three heavies and four from the control set.

from rebound_runs import bin_analysis 
from scipy.interpolate import interp1d
reload(bin_analysis)
%pylab inline

base='/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/control/'
names=np.genfromtxt(base+'/names', dtype=str)
tab=[]
for ii,name in enumerate(names):
    #idx=np.where(np.genfromtxt(base+name.replace('.bin', '_masses'))>1.0e-4)[0][0]+1
    bins=bin_analysis.BinAnalysis(base+name)
    ts=np.genfromtxt((base+name).replace('.bin', '_times'))
    ms=np.genfromtxt((base+name).replace('.bin', '_masses'))
    champ=bins.bin_pairs_sort(extra='_light')[-1]
    a_champ=np.mean(bins.bins[bins.pairs==champ][:,4])
    i1, i2=champ
    mmin, mmax=min([ms[i1-1], ms[i2-1]]), max([ms[i1-1], ms[i2-1]])
    
    tab.append([name,ts[-1]/(2.*np.pi),np.sort(bins.bin_times(norm=False,extra='_light',total=True))[-1]/(2.*np.pi), mmin, mmax, i1, i2, a_champ])

from astropy.table import Table

tab_control=Table(rows=tab,names=['run', 'length', 'max_bin', 'm1', 'm2', 'i1', 'i2', 'abar'])
tab_control[np.argsort(tab_control['max_bin'])][::-1][:20]

from scipy.interpolate import interp1d

bases=['/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/imax_5_Nh_1_m5e-3/',\
      '/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/imax_5_Nh_10/', 
      '/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/control/']
#bases=['/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/control/']

t_std=np.arange(0.2*np.pi, 495*2.*np.pi, 0.2*np.pi)
v_avg=np.zeros([len(bases), len(t_std)])
for ii,base in enumerate(bases):
    names=np.genfromtxt(base+'/names', dtype=str)
    vs_all=[]
    for jj,name in enumerate(names):
        vs=np.genfromtxt(base+name.replace('.bin', '_sigs_low'))
        ts=np.genfromtxt(base+name.replace('.bin', '_times'))
        if ts[-1]<t_std[-1]:
            print jj, name
            continue
        vs=vs[:,2]
        vs_all.append(interp1d(ts, vs)(t_std))
    v_avg[ii]=np.mean(vs_all, axis=0)

from astropy.table import Table

names = np.genfromtxt('/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/imax_5_Nh_10/names',dtype=str)
amin=1
nbins=20
idx=0
sigs=np.zeros(nbins)
base="/home/aleksey/Dropbox/projects/disk_binaries/sim_data/circ_disk_100_mass_spec/imax_5_Nh_10/"
a_ords=np.array([1+2*float(jj)/nbins for jj in range(nbins)])
for jj in range(nbins):
    a_in=amin+float(2*jj)/nbins
    a_out=amin+float(2*(jj+1))/nbins
    vs=[]
    vs_all=[]
    for name in names:
        tab=Table.read(base+name.replace('.bin', '_vs.h5'), path='bin/{0}'.format(idx))
        vs.append(np.array(tab[(a_in<=tab['a'])& (tab['a']<a_out)]['vz']))
        vs_all.append(np.array(tab['vz']))
    sigs[jj]=np.std(np.concatenate(vs))
    sig_all=np.std(np.concatenate(vs_all))
